         <div type="entry">
                <head>Sauget, Joseph-Marie</head>
                <ab type="idnos">
                    <idno type="URI">https://gedsh.bethmardutho.org/Sauget-Joseph-Marie</idno>
                    <idno type="syriaca-bibl">http://syriaca.org/bibl/482</idno>
                    <idno type="entry">473</idno>
                    <milestone unit="pages" n="360"/>
                    <idno type="althead" subtype="altorder">Joseph-Marie Sauget</idno>
                    <idno type="subject">http://syriaca.org/person/719</idno>
                    <note type="type">person</note>
                    <note type="abstract">Scriptor in the Vatican Library (1958-88), and author of
                        numerous valuable studies on Syriac and Christian Arabic literature.<note/>
                    </note>
                </ab>
                <ab type="infobox">(1926–88)</ab>
                <div type="body">
                    <p>Scriptor in the Vatican Library (1958–88), and author of numerous valuable
                        studies on Syriac and Christian Arabic literature. His books include a
                        bibliography of oriental liturgical rites, covering 1900–60 (1962), a
                        pioneering study of Melkite synaxaria (Subsidia Hagiographica 45, 1969), two
                        monographs on <abbr>mss.</abbr> in the Borgia collection (Syr. 39: <abbr>SeT</abbr> 292, 1981; and
                        Syr. 60, a Gazza: <abbr>SeT</abbr> 326, 1987), and a study of an Arabic translation of
                        the Saying of the Fathers in the Paradise of <ref rend="bold" target="https://gedsh.bethmardutho.org/Enanisho">
                            <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/474">ʿEnanishoʿ</persName>
                        </ref> (<abbr>CSCO</abbr>
                        495, 1987).</p>
                </div>
                <div type="bibl">
                    <head>Sources</head>
                    <listBibl>
                        <bibl>J.-M. Sauget (<abbr>ed.</abbr> L. Duval-Arnould and F. Rilliet), <title rend="italic">Littératures et manuscrits des chrétientés syriaques
                                et arabes</title> (<abbr>SeT</abbr> 389; 1998). (a selection of his articles, and
                            his bibliography).</bibl>
                    </listBibl>
                </div>
